{"word":"ἀρωγός","slug":"ἀρωγός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀρωγός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀρήγω'><el>ἀρήγω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>aiding, succouring, propitious, serviceable</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>serviceable towards</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a helper, aid</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> in battle, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <i>a defender</i> before a tribunal, <i>advocate</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}